[[Captain/Legends|Captain]] '''Orliss Gillmunn''' was [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] who was one of a handful of [[Jabiimi]] leaders who escaped [[Alto Stratus]]'s [[Political coup on Jabiim|purge]] of the [[Jabiim Congress]].

==Biography==
Gillmunn rallied the forces loyal to the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and fought to win back the planet. Gillmunn believed that the Republic would do anything to support the Jabiimi Loyalists. However, when Republic forces surrendered the planet to the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatists]], acting planetary commander [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] used the limited evacuation dropships available to retrieve the Republic's own [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]], leaving the Jabiimi loyalists behind with the words, "This is your war now."<ref name="Battle of Jabiim 4" /> Captain Gillmunn felt betrayed and swore his people would never forget what the Republic had done. The [[20 BBY/Legends|next year]], during the fighting, he was killed by [[Thorne Kraym]] in the [[Massacre at High Rock Canyon]].

Gillmunn was the [[Parent/Legends|father]] of the future leader of the Jabiimi Resistance against the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], [[Nolan Gillmunn]].

